snippet: The changes along Avenue Habib Bourguiba reflect the tumult in Tunisia two years after a revolution deposed a president and ushered in an era of uncertainty.
abstract: Tunis Journal; changes along Avenue Habib Bourguiba in Tunis, named for Tunisia's first post-independence president, reflect tumult and cautious hope two years after 2011 revolution deposed Pres Zine el-Abidine Ben Ali and ushered in era of uncertainty.
lead_paragraph: The changes along Avenue Habib Bourguiba reflect the tumult in Tunisia two years after a revolution deposed a president and ushered in an era of uncertainty.
